                <h2 class="text-information-title">WHAT ARE THE BENEFITS OF RATING WATER HEATING?</h2>
                <p class="text-information">Rainwater is cheap, and with very little trace of impurities, all personal need is to obtain storage media and rain. Water treatment costs are also low and easy to do without professionals. Rainwater harvesting provides a reliable alternative water source in areas where they experience water scarcity and an additional source where there are no problems with water allowing people to direct it towards purposes. other uses such as irrigation or electricity generation. Rainwater also drastically reduces water bills; it can be used interchangeably with ordinary water but for other tasks such as laundry that consumes large amounts of water.</p>
                <p><b>DANGEROUS RATING WATER</b></p>
                <p class="text-information">As much as water from rain is pure, it sometimes runs off surfaces that can contain impurities that can be dangerous to humans. Most homes in the developing world are made of corrugated iron sheets that rust over time; when rainwater washes away rust into the cistern, drinking this water can lead to health complications. Some roofing materials contain high levels of lead and asbestos which are toxic to the human body if consumed directly. </p>
                <p class="text-information">Some areas in the developed world are heavily industrialized which means very high levels of air pollution. When rainwater mixes with certain chemicals in the air, the water becomes acidic and unsuitable for use. Untreated rainwater is the source of dangerous waterborne diseases such as skin poisoning and cholera that can lead to death if left untreated.</p>
                <div class="col-sm-5">

                    <img class="image" src="../image/picture 10.jpg" alt="" >
                
                </div>
