        <h6><b>METHODS OF REPAIR STORAGE</b></h6><br>
                    <b>Building underground rainwater tank:</b>
                    <p class="text-information">Underground water tank is a necessary work for every apartment, family, and agency. Used to store  water for domestic use as well as production. However, you need to let the groundwater tank no chance to leak. As well as ensuring the quality of the underground water tank. </p>
                    <ins>Advantages of building an underground water tank</ins>
                    <p class="text-information">The advantage of building a water tank is that it can be used for many years, firmly, and is difficult to break due to external influences. However, the reality shows that this type of water tank brings a lot of risks and risks to the health of users and affects the living environment.</p>
                    <div class="col-sm-5">

                        <img class="image" src="../image/pic 12.jpg" alt="" >
                    
                    </div>
                    <ins>Disadvantages of concrete water tanks include:</ins>
                    <p class="text-information">
                        Easy to absorb dirty water from the outside into the tank because the system has an unstable lid, not tight enough. This will cause dangerous water pollution.
                    Self-built water tanks face the risk of cracking, subsidence, tilting because the system does not have its own cellar, close to the ground or built in an area where the soil has been eroded due to heavy rain or underground circuit. </p>
                    <p class="text-information">
                        Can become a shelter and decompose the carcasses of some animals and insects such as mice, cockroaches, mosquitoes, etc., affecting the water source and living environment of the whole family.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-information">
                        Easy to form algae, contaminated by contaminated water sources, harmful microorganisms.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-information">
                        Traditional concrete underground water tanks also make it difficult to clean the tanks due to the inconvenient water inlet and outlet systems. Even old buildings do not have a drainage system below.
                    </p>
                    <div class="col-sm-5">

                        <img class="image" src="../image/pic 13.jpg" alt="" >
                    
