                    <p class="text-information" style="padding-top: 10px;">It is not natural that since its appearance, stainless steel water tanks are preferred. Because there are many outstanding advantages compared to other types of material water tanks that have appeared before.</p>
                    <p class="text-information">Ensure the safety of the water source: The water tank is usually located on a high place (the terrace or the roof), so the temperature of the water may be abnormally hot/cold. Because stainless steel can be affected by solar heat. However, whether the temperature is high or low, the water quality is still the same, ensuring safety for the family to use.</p>
                    <p class="text-information">Durability comes with time: 3 decades ago, stainless steel water tanks began to be widely used. Because of the durability of stainless steel, the use time can be up to dozens of years (maximum 30 years). Moreover, stainless steel tanks are difficult to be shaken and shaken when external forces occur (such as rain, wind, storm, ...).</p>
                    <p class="text-information">Many different sizes and capacities: Stainless steel tanks are also preferred because they are manufactured in different sizes. Because each family will have different number of members and needs. Previously, water tanks of other materials only had a few sizes, leading to a lack of - excess when used. But with the variety of stainless steel sinks, any family can find a suitable capacity.</p>
                    <p class="text-information">Many places to sell and buy easily: Currently, almost all construction stores sell stainless steel water tanks. Therefore, you can find and buy easily, without having to transport as far as before.</p>
                    <b><ins>What are the disadvantages of stainless steel water tanks?</ins></b>
                    <p class="text-information">Of course, any product will have both advantages and disadvantages, more or less, and so does the stainless steel water tank. Compared with the advantages, the disadvantages of using the tub are less, but you should still be careful.</p>
                    <p class="text-information">The cost of buying stainless steel water tanks is higher: Compared with other materials, stainless steel tanks are classified as tanks with higher costs. Because the stainless steel material is durable, the value is higher than the rest of the tubs.</p>
                    <p class="text-information">Risk of damage when encountering water with impurities: Stainless steel helps to maintain water quality but that is with normal water. There are places where the water is contaminated with alum, saline, containing impurities that affect stainless steel.</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li><b>Reusable Reservoir:</b> Ellipse Tank modules assembled into flexible sized blocks, wrapped in high strength HDPE waterproofing to store water. This stored water can then be used for watering plants, cleaning, fire protection, etc.</li>
                        <li><b>Temporary storage reservoir:</b> Ellipse Tank modules are assembled into flexible sized underground blocks, wrapped in geotextile. The amount of rainwater temporarily stored will slowly penetrate into the surrounding environment, replenish groundwater and increase humidity for the area.</li>
                    </ol>
                    <b>The advantages of the solution:</b><br>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Drainage to prevent waterlogging in the garden</li>
                        <li>Maximize use of surface land to plant trees.</li>
                        <li>Recover water to the storage lake for reuse for garden irrigation.</li>
                        <li>Simple construction, time saving, low cost.</li>
                        <li>Minimize environmental pollution such as waterlogging, odors, avoid mosquitoes and insects, harmful organisms...</li>
                        <li>Increase garden aesthetics and be environmentally friendly</li>
